data.title: The 'Clerks' Have A Comeback
data.meta_description: Jay, Silent Bob And Others Come Out For The Premiere Of 'Clerks II'
data.text:
"Clerks II" costars Jason Mewes, left, and Kevin Smith pose together at the premiere of the film in Los Angeles on July 11, 2006. Mewes and Smith reprised their roles as the popular characters Jay and Silent Bob.

Rosario Dawson arrives at the premiere of "Clerks II" in Los Angeles on July 11, 2006. Dawson plays Becky in the film, which opens on July 21.

Jason Mewes, left, cops a feel from his "Clerks II" costar Jason Lee at the premiere of the film at the Cinerama Dome Theater in Los Angeles on July 11, 2006. Both Mewes and Lee are veterans of previous Kevin Smith films -- Mewes starred in the original "Clerks" and both actors were in "Jay and Silent Bob Strike Back."

Writer-director Kevin Smith poses with his wife, Jennifer Schwalbach, and their daughter, Harley, as they arrive at the premiere of "Clerks II" at the Cinerama Dome Theater in Los Angeles on July 11, 2006. Both Smith and Schwalbach have roles in the film.

Kristen Bell poses for photographers at the premiere of "Clerks II" in Los Angeles on July 11, 2006. The movie picks up 10 years after the original left off.

Brian O'Halloran arrives at the premiere of "Clerks II" in Los Angeles on July 11, 2006. O'Halloran plays Dante in the film, which opens July 21.

Actress Eliza Dushku arrives at the premiere of the MGM film "Clerks II" in Los Angeles on July 11, 2006. The movie opens nationwide on July 21.

Ali Larter arrives at the premiere of the film "Clerks II" at the Cinerama Dome Theater in Los Angeles on July 11, 2006. The story picks up 10 years after the antics of the original "Clerks" film.

Actor Trevor Fehrman arrives at the premiere of "Clerks II" in Los Angeles on July 11, 2006. Fehrman plays Elias, an employee at a fast-food restaurant, in the film.

Rosario Dawson embraces her "Clerks II" writer-director-costar Kevin Smith at the premiere of the film at the Cinerama Dome Theater in Los Angeles on July 11, 2006. Smith had originally claimed he would not do another Clerks film after 2001's "Jay and Silent Bob Strike Back," but changed his mind when he was working on the "Clerks" 10th anniversary DVD and remembered how much he loved the characters.

Actress Courtney Hansen poses for photographers at the premiere of the MGM film "Clerks II" in Los Angeles on July 11, 2006. The film hits theaters on July 21.

Actor Jake Richardson arrives at the premiere of "Clerks II" at Los Angeles' Cinerama Dome Theater on July 11, 2006. The film starts 10 years after the original "Clerks" left off.

Comedian Earthquake, from left, and actors Trevor Fehrman and Jake Richardson pose at the after-party for the premiere of the MGM film "Clerks II" at Avelon in Los Angeles on July 11, 2006. The film hits theaters on July 21.

"Clerks II" star Rosario Dawson poses with her boyfriend, fellow actor Jason Lewis, at the after-party for the premiere of her film in Los Angeles on July 11, 2006.

Kevin Smith, left, and producer Scott Mosier pose at the after-party for the premiere of "Clerks II" at Avelon in Los Angeles on July 11, 2006. The film hits theaters on July 21.
